{"title_page": "2018 Arkansas Razorbacks football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n|year = 2018\n|team = Arkansas Razorbacks\n|sport = football\n|logo = Arkansas Razorbacks logo.svg\n|logo_size = 250px\n|logo_alt = Arkansas Razorbacks logo\n|conference = Southeastern Conference\n|division = Western Division\n|short_conf = SEC\n|CoachRank = \n|APRank = \n|CFPRank = \n|record = 2\u201310\n|conf_record = 0\u20138\n|head_coach = [[Chad Morris]]\n|hc_year= 1st\n|off_coach = [[Joe Craddock]]\n|oc_year= 1st\n|def_coach = [[John Chavis (American football)|John Chavis]]\n|dc_year= 1st\n|off_scheme = \n|def_scheme = [[4\u20133 defense|4\u20133]]\n|captain={{plainlist|\n*Santos Ramirez <small>(senior DB)</small>\n*Hjalte Froholdt <small>(senior OL)</small>\n*Dre Greenlaw <small>(senior LB)</small>\n*De'Jon Harris <small>(junior LB)</small>\n}}\n|stadium = [[Donald W. Reynolds Razorback Stadium]]<br>(Capacity: 76,212)<br>\n[[War Memorial Stadium (Arkansas)|War Memorial Stadium]] <small>''(Alternate)''</small><br>(Capacity: 54,120)\n|champion =\n|bowl = \n|bowl_result = \n}}\n{{2018 SEC football standings}}\nThe '''2018 Arkansas Razorbacks football team''' represented the [[University of Arkansas]] in the [[2018 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The Razorbacks played their home games at [[Donald W. Reynolds Razorback Stadium]] in [[Fayetteville, Arkansas]], with one home game at [[War Memorial Stadium (Arkansas)|War Memorial Stadium]] in [[Little Rock, Arkansas|Little Rock]]. Arkansas played as a member of the Western Division of the [[Southeastern Conference]] (SEC). The Razorbacks were led by first-year head coach [[Chad Morris]]. They finished the season 2\u201310, 0\u20138 in SEC play to finish in last place in the Western Division.\n\n==Previous season==\n{{main|2017 Arkansas Razorbacks football team}}\nThe [[2017 Arkansas Razorbacks football team|Razorbacks]] finished the [[2017 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2017 season]] 4\u20138, 1\u20137 in [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]] play to finish in last place in the Western Division.\n\n==Preseason==\n===Position key===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|[[Running back|Back]]\n|'''B'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Center (American football)|Center]]\n|'''C'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Cornerback]]\n|'''CB'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Defensive back]]\n|'''DB'''\n|-\n|[[Defensive end]]\n|'''DE'''\n|[[Defensive lineman]]\n|'''DL'''\n|[[Defensive tackle]]\n|'''DT'''\n|[[End (American football)|End]]\n|'''E'''\n|-\n|[[Fullback (American football)|Fullback]]\n|'''FB'''\n|[[Guard (American football)|Guard]]\n|'''G'''\n|[[Halfback (American football)|Halfback]]\n|'''HB'''\n|[[Placekicker|Kicker]]\n|'''K'''\n|-\n|[[Kickoff returner]]\n|'''KR'''\n|[[Offensive tackle]]\n|'''OT'''\n|[[Lineman (American football)|Offensive lineman]]\n|'''OL'''\n|[[Linebacker]]\n|'''LB'''\n|-\n|[[Long snapper]]\n|'''LS'''\n|[[Punter (American football)|Punter]]\n|'''P'''\n|[[Punt returner]]\n|'''PR'''\n|[[Quarterback]]\n|'''QB'''\n|-\n|[[Running back]]\n|'''RB'''\n|[[Safety (American and Canadian football position)|Safety]]\n|'''S'''\n|[[Tight end]]\n|'''TE'''\n|[[Wide receiver]]\n|'''WR'''\n|}\n\n===Recruits===\nThe Razorbacks signed a total of 17 recruits.\n{{College Athlete Recruit Start|40=no|collapse=yes|year=2018}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit  = Connor Noland\n| position = QB\n| hometown = [[Greenwood, Arkansas]]\n| highschool = [[Greenwood High School (Arkansas)|Greenwood High School]]\n| feet   = 6\n| inches = 3\n| weight = 205\n| commitdate = July 20, 2016\n| scout stars  = 4\n| rivals stars = 3\n| 247 stars = 3\n| espn stars = 4\n}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit  = Bumper Pool\n| position = LB\n| hometown = [[Lucas, Texas]]\n| highschool = [[Lovejoy High School (Lucas, Texas)|Lovejoy High School]]\n| feet   = 