=\"4\"  style=\"font-size:8pt; text-align:center;\"|'''Reference:'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arkansasrazorbacks.com/sport/m-footbl/roster/#coaches |title=Arkansas Razorbacks 2017-18 Coaching Staff |website=arkansasrazorbacks.com |publisher=University of Arkansas |access-date=January 4, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n====Coaching changes====\n[[Chad Morris]], former head coach at [[Southern Methodist University]], was hired on December 6, 2017, to be the 33rd head coach of the Arkansas Razorbacks,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arkansasrazorbacks.com/chad-morris-named-head-football-coach/ |title=Chad Morris named head football coach |website=arkansasrazorbacks.com |publisher=University of Arkansas |date=December 6, 2017 |access-date=January 4, 2018}}</ref> following the dismissal of [[Bret Bielema]] just under two weeks prior.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arkansasrazorbacks.com/bielema-dismissed-as-head-football-coach/ |title=Bielema dismissed as head football coach|website=arkansasrazorbacks.com |publisher=University of Arkansas |date=November 24, 2017 |access-date=January 4, 2018}}</ref> On January 9, 2018, [[Joe Craddock]] was named offensive coordinator,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arkansasrazorbacks.com/craddock-named-offensive-coordinator-and-qbs-coach/ |title=Craddock named Offensive Coordinator and QBs coach |last=Langlois |first=Brandon |date=January 9, 2018 |website=arkansasrazorbacks.com |publisher=University of Arkansas |access-date=January 15, 2018}}</ref> and [[John Chavis (American football)|John Chavis]] was named defensive coordinator.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arkansasrazorbacks.com/chavis-named-defensive-coordinator/ |title=Chavis named Defensive Coordinator and LBs coach |last=Langlois |first=Brandon |date=January 9, 2018 |website=arkansasrazorbacks.com |publisher=University of Arkansas |access-date=January 15, 2018}}</ref> Both had previously served the same roles at SMU and [[Texas A&M University|Texas A&M]], respectively.\n\n[[Barry Lunney Jr.]], the tight ends coach, and John Scott Jr., a defensive line coach, were the only two assistants retained, and will enter their sixth and second seasons, respectively, in their current positions with the Razorbacks.\n\n===Roster===\n{{American football roster/Header|year=2018|team=Arkansas Razorbacks|teamcolors=y\n|offensive_players=\n{{American football roster/Player|num=1|class=SR|first=Jared|last=Cornelius|pos=WR}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=2|class=SO|first=Chase|last=Hayden|pos=RB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=3|class=FR|rs=y|first=Koilan|last=Jackson|pos=WR}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=4|class=JR|first=Ty|last=Storey|pos=QB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=5|class=SO|rs=y|first=Rakeem|last=Boyd|link=y|pos=RB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=6|class=JR|first=T. J.|last=Hammonds|pos=RB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=7|class=SR|first=Jonathan|last=Nance|pos=WR}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=8|class=FR|first=Michael|last=Woods|pos=WR}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=9|class=SO|first=De'Vion|last=Warren|pos=WR}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=10|class=SO|first=Jordan|last=Jones|pos=WR}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=11|class=FR|rs=y|first=Daulton|last=Hyatt|pos=QB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=13|class=JR|first=Deon|last=Stewart|pos=WR}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=14|class=FR|rs=y|first=Maleek|last=Barkley|pos=RB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=14|class=SO|first=Carson|last=Proctor|pos=QB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=15|class=SO|first=Cole|last=Kelley|pos=QB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=16|class=JR|first=La'Michael|last=Pettway|pos=WR}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=17|class=FR|first=Austin|last=Aune|pos=QB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=18|class=SO|first=Jack|last=Lindsey|pos=QB}}\n{{American football roster/Player|num=18|class=SR|first=Jeremy|last=Patton|pos=TE}}\n{{American football rost