tyle-traditional-fire/ |title=Modern Style + Traditional \ud83d\udd25 |last=McGillis |first=Trevor |date=July 10, 2018 |website=arkansasrazorbacks.com |publisher=University of Arkansas |access-date=July 17, 2018}}\n</ref>\n*'''July 20, 2018:''' The SEC media poll was released, and placed the Razorbacks last out of the seven teams in the SEC West. The Hogs received 412 votes, 166 shy of sixth-place Ole Miss.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/ncaaf/sec/2018/07/20/alabama-georgia-dominate-preseason-sec-college-football-media-poll/807832002/ |title=Alabama, Georgia dominate preseason SEC college football media poll |date=July 20, 2018 |publisher=USA Today |access-date=July 20, 2018}}</ref>\n*'''July 21, 2018:''' The Razorbacks had three players selected to the preseason all-SEC teams. The second-team offense featured OL Hjalte Froholdt, and the third-team defense featured LB De'Jon Harris and DB Santos Ramirez.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.secsports.com/article/24148392/media-predicts-alabama-win-2018-sec-championship |title=Media predicts Alabama to win 2018 SEC Championship |date=July 21, 2018 |website=secsports.com |publisher=Southeastern Conference |access-date=July 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Award watch lists===\n<small>Listed in the order that they were released</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Arkansas Razorbacks|Award|Player|Position|Year}}\n|-\n|[[Chuck Bednarik Award]]<ref>{{cite web|title=2018 Bednarik Award Watch List|url=https://www.maxwellfootballclub.org/2018-maxwell-bednarik-watch-list|date=July 16, 2018|accessdate=July 16, 2018}}</ref>\n|De'Jon Harris\n|Linebacker\n|Junior\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Doak Walker Award]]<ref>{{cite web|title=2018 Doak Walker Award Candidates|url=https://www.smu.edu/DoakWalkerAward/Candidates|date=July 18, 2018|accessdate=July 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|Chase Hayden\n|Running back\n|Sophomore\n|-\n|Devwah Whaley\n|Running back\n|Junior\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Butkus Award]]<ref>{{cite web |url=ht