It was broadcast on the [[SEC Network]].<ref name= \"schedule\">{{cite web |url=http://www.fbschedules.com/ncaa-18/2018-arkansas-razorbacks-football-schedule.php |title=2018 Arkansas Razorbacks football schedule |website=fbschedules.com |publisher=FB Schedules |access-date=April 6, 2018}}</ref> The white team consisted of the offense and the red team consisted of the defense.\n\nThe spring game followed a different format: the game was played in twelve minute quarters, rather than fifteen, with a running clock in the second half. The game was scored traditionally on offense (white team), but the defense (red team) could earn points for a variety of achievements (6 pts. for touchdown, 3 for turnover or 4th down stop, 2 for three-and-out, 2 for blocked kick, 1 for sack or TFL).<ref name= \"spring\">{{cite web |url=http://www.arkansasonline.com/news/2018/apr/07/live-updates-arkansas-spring-game/ |title=Recapping Arkansas' spring game |last=Bordelon |first=Scottie |date=April 7, 2018 |website=arkansasonline.com |publisher=ArkansasOnline |access-date=April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n! Date !! Time !! Spring Game !! Site !! TV !! Result !! Attendance !! Source\n|-\n|April 7||1:00&nbsp;p.m.||Red vs. White Spring Game|| [[War Memorial Stadium (Arkansas)|War Memorial Stadium]] \u2022 [[Little Rock, Arkansas|Little Rock, AR]] || [[SEC Network|SECN]] || '''White''' 27\u201325 || style=\"text-align:center\"|7,000 || style=text-align:center|<ref name=\"spring\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arkansasrazorbacks.com/stats/football/2018/RedWhiteResults.pdf |title=White vs. Red Results |date=April 7, 2018 |website=arkansasrazorbacks.com |publisher=University of Arkansas |access-date=April 9, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Schedule==\nThe Razorbacks' 2018 schedule consisted of 7 home games, 4 away games, and 1 neutral game in the regular season. The Razorbacks hosted SEC foes [[Alabama Crimson Tide football|Alabama]], [[Ole Miss Rebels football|Ole Miss]] (in [[Little Rock, Arkansas|Little Rock]]), [[Vanderbilt Commodores football|Vanderbilt]], and [[LSU Tigers football|LSU]], and traveled to [[Auburn Tigers football|Auburn]], [[Mississippi State Bulldogs football|Mississippi State]], and [[Missouri Tigers football|Missouri]]. Arkansas played against [[Texas A&M Aggies football|Texas A&M]] in [[Arlington, Texas]] for the [[Arkansas\u2013Texas A&M football rivalry|fifth year in a row]].\n\nArkansas hosted three of its four of its non\u2013conference games: against [[Eastern Illinois Panthers football|Eastern Illinois]] from the [[Ohio Valley Conference]], [[North Texas Mean Green football|North Texas]] from [[Conference USA]], and [[Tulsa Golden Hurricane football|Tulsa]] from the [[American Athletic Conference]]. The lone away non\u2013conference game saw the Hogs travel to [[Fort Collins, Colorado]] to play [[Colorado State Rams football|Colorado State]], from the [[Mountain West Conference]].\n\nPer southernpigskin.com, the Razorbacks' schedule ranked as the 39th-toughest of the 66 Power Five teams in the nation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.southernpigskin.com/sec/2018-strength-of-schedule-rankings/ |title=2018 Strength of Schedule Rankings |last=Smith |first=Matt |website=southernpigskin.com |publisher=Southern Pigskin |access-date=April 7, 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{CFB schedule\n| opprank = y\n| rankyear = 2018\n| rankdivision = NCAA Division I FBS\n| poll = AP\n| timezone = Central\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n|date = September 1\n|time = 3:00 p.m.\n|opponent = [[2018 Eastern Illinois Panthers football team|Eastern Illinois]]<ncg>\n|stadium = [[Donald W. Reynolds Razorback Stadium]]\n|cityst = [[Fayetteville, Arkansas|Fayetteville, AR]]\n|tv = [[SEC Network|SECN]]\n|w/l = w\n|score = 55\u201320\n|attend = 63,342\n|source = <ref name= \"eiu-nt\">{{cite web |url=https://247sports.com/college/arkansas/Article/Game-times-for-Arkansas-Razorbacks-football-2018-Eastern-Illinois-Colorado-State-North-Texas-118668381/ |titl